ce","Vitre, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France":"Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France","Élan, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Élan, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"von","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Rethel","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German (<b>Räthel</b>): perhaps from a pet form of   Rath   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Rath","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Hans, Kurt, Erna, Fritz, Lutz, Orlo, Reinhart, Arno, Bernd, Gerhardt, Hermann.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): descriptive epithet for a wise person or counselor, from Middle High German <i>rāt</i> ‘counsel, advice’, German <i>Rat</i> ‘counsel, advice’, also ‘stock, supply’.","German; Swiss German (<b>Räth</b>): from a short form of any of various ancient Germanic compound personal names formed with <i>rād</i>, <i>rāt</i> ‘counsel, advice’ as the first element. This surname is also found in France (Alsace and Lorraine)."]}]},{"name":"Manasses","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Forgetfulness"],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Manasses von Rethel IV was born about 1140, in Rethel, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France, his father, Gauthier \"le Dévôt\" de Réthel comte de Rethel, was 41 and his mother, Beatrix of Namur, was 31. He had at least 1 son with Mathilde von Kyrburg. He died about 1198, in his hometown, at the age of 60, and was buried in Élan, Ardennes, Champagne-Ardenne, France."},"et":{"environ 